==English==
=== Etymology===
A corruption of "box standard" originating in conversations about cars for racing. The corruption was possibly the result of different british accents.
===Adjective===
'''bog standard'''
# {{Idiom}} Especially [[plain]], [[ordinary]], or [[unremarkable]]; having no special, excess or unusual [[feature]]s; plain [[vanilla]]
#:''She drives a bog standard economy car.''